rComments: Gives a decent lecture however extremly boring. She comes off a little harsh, I was shocked to see another review on here on how she replies to questions.. Its true. She has literally almost always cut off a student while speaking before actually hearing what they have to say. Shes VERY vague on what will be on midterms and tests on purpose..

Professor Baird is amazing, but for this course, you do not need much to succeed, just read the textbook and do the practice quizzes she posts weekly and you will be good. For that reason, the book tends to be kind of repetitive and boring sometimes, but overall it's a great course with her. evaluations are based on 2midterms and a final, all MCQ.

Who knew statistics could be so entertaining! Professor Baird is super funny during her lectures regardless of what we are learning. I did not need to use the textbook once during the class, as all information was presented in class. Test questions rely on your understanding of the material rather than entering large computations into a calculator

Dr. Baird is a very good teacher, but the course itself is a little boring and difficult to learn from. Most content required is included in lectures, but the page-by-page format learning style makes it feel a little disconnected. Reading and understanding the textbook is probably enough to pass. Practice Quizzes are very helpful.

Dr. Baird is such a funny prof, which keeps the class engaging. She is very detailed in her explanations which is great for statistics, as it can be a tricky subject to understand. The textbook she assigned had long chapters, so the readings took a good chunk of time.

I think this is the only time I've ever understood math. Love this prof. She clearly enjoys her job and makes her lectures very easy to understand. She cares a lot about the application of formulas rather than just computations. Quiz questions reappear on tests and the final exam!!!!
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Accessible outside class', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Professor Baird is amazing, she is one of a kind! I would differently take her again. We only had 2 midterms and one final, all very straightforward with plenty of time to complete each. Be aware that she cares about application-based material rather than the math itself. In other words, UNDERSTAND IT and you will succeed in her course.

Dr. Baird clearly loves statistics and tries to make it as pleasant of an experience as she can. She provides practice quizzes which help a LOT and her exams (2 mid 1 final) are MC. If you study and make the effort to understand and make a good cribb sheet then you will do great. The class avg for our final was 85%, take stats with her!!
I hate math but I actually enjoyed her stats class. Shes super funny and helpful and does her best to ensure we understand. She was the best!

Felt like I was teaching myself based on an outdated blog. She spells things incorrectly and the information she provides you is incomplete. I did a test based on her notes and got things wrong on the test THAT WERE DIRECTLY FROM HER NOTES! Drop her class unless you like self-taught textbook reading (it's your only hope)!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: It's a bird course but be prepared to learn it all on your own.
an absolute sweetheart. tries her best to make you comfortable with her class and wants her students to succeed. positive vibe and always happy.
Dr. Baird is so funny! She honestly is the best stats prof I've ever had! Her tests are super easy and exactly whats covered in class and on the quizzes so no stress!

Hands down, the best professor I've had in uni yet. Somehow prof. Baird makes stats easy to learn, and is so charismatic while she teaches. Having her as a prof for 2106 made 2116 a JOKE, you can get through 75% of 2116 just from her teachings alone. DO NOT skip lectures, they were crucial to effectively learning the content.

Stats is hard in any subject, but Prof. Baird makes it SO MUCH BETTER. She cares about her students and constantly reminds you to stay calm and to focus. Exams are very fair. She gives tons of hints about what will be on them. DGD's are great. This was my first time getting a good mark in a math-based class.

Professor Baird is hilarious and engaging, her lectures are well worth attending. Tests aren't bad but you need to know the material. My only issue with her is that she's harsh and impatient when answering questions, and cuts students off before they even fully explain what they're asking. Don't go to her for extra help.

Did well in the class because shes definitely good at teaching but I absolutely did NOT like her as a professor. She was rude and very unsympathetic towards students. Gets irritated if you ask her a simple question and will call you out in front of everyone. Overall shes good at teaching!!

Shes good at her job and has amazing lectures! Easy to understand without having to read the textbook. Work hard and youll get a good grade. Assignments are good grade boosters. She can be funny here and there but also very harsh as well. She did intimidate me by yelling at a student for some breezy giggling and rolling her eyes consistently.
Arrogant, rude, unsympathetic, and overall not the nicest person I've dealt with. She's good at her stuff but being a prof also requires manners which she doesn't have.

Brenda Baird is a great professor! She is really well at explaining the material and her exams are not that difficult if you study. The only thing that I disliked about her is the fact how she can be utterly rude if you ask her a question in terms of the class and the fact that she thinks its amusing to call people out and embarrass them.

She understands her topic and her explanations are pretty good. Ive had better professors but shes still above average. She did however intimidate me with her response to a homework question I emailed her about. Shes also not very understanding when it comes to deferrals of any sort. All in all, shes a very smart lady and can teach quite well.

The teacher is great and allowed us to bring in a double-sided cheat sheet to both mid-terms and the final exam -lab is important to attend as it helps clear up things and the TA always dropped hints for the exams -there was two assignments that were super easy and mark boosters

Baird is an amazing professor! Lectures are engaging, interesting, and genuinely enjoyable. The class material isnt difficult to grasp, but you need to attend lectures to do well because she goes in depth and tells you exactly what the long answer questions on exams will be. Marked on 2 midterms and a final. You need to take child psych with her!
I am terrible at math but she made stats enjoyable and easy! it's not hard to do well in this class, take it!

Good prof, gives slides but you have to take notes because most of what she says isn't on the slides and is test material. I bought the book, total waste of money, barely ever used it except for a couple definitions that weren't clear. Exams are easy and straight forward. Pay attention and she tells you exactly what the long answer questions are.

She is a nice person. BUT Very strict for short answer and long answer question. If your english is not good enough, please choose other professor. Need to attend her lectures every class, and write things for her preference.

I loved having her as a prof. She moves through topics at an easy enough pace, while covering everything that needs to be covered. You can tell she loves what she does and it makes it interesting for everyone.

Baird has an amazing personality, but if you don't understand her or the class material you're basically screwed. She essentially just reviews the textbook in class, but adds a few important details; so if you don't have time to read before class you'll be confused. She can be condescending with questions, but if you study LOTS you'll be fine

Dr. Baird is a nice and funny woman. She teaches at a slower pace than average which is nice because she explains concepts and theories thoroughly. There are no papers for her class, just 2 midterms and a final which is nice. She often rambles about one topic for a long time but that's because she's passionate about child psychology.

I love Professor Baird. She's so understanding when it comes to statistics because it's a scary class for a lot of students to take. She goes super slow so everyone understands and she makes jokes so that's a plus as well.
she's so great

She was very enthusiastic about statistics and made the intro course easy to understand. I would recommend going to the lectures because although she posts the slides, she gives helpful hints and tricks in class. Her assignments are pretty easy and she doesn't change the questions on them per semester. Overall a good professor.

Make sure you keep up with your readings because the final exam is based on the textbook. Her lectures are not based on the textbook but on her lecture material which is not 100% the same so make lecture notes for the midterms and notes from the textbook for the final.

Funny prof and easy class if you have taken math before. However, spends too much time on the easy material and rushes the challenging stuff. Also doesn't listen to your questions and then gets mad when people don't answer her questions. Stopped attending, did the text q's, got nearly perfect. She makes things more confusing than has to be

Her lectures are amazing, and her midterms/exam are straightforward. You only need to go to class and study her slides for midterms. Once midterms are over, theres no need to go to lectures because the exam is based only on the textbook. The class is a very easy A, I highly recommend taking it.

Professor Baird is very, very knowledgeable and passionate about her subject. She makes her lectures interesting, & enjoyable. I recommend going to class, it helps to fill in some information. Only downside is that her 2nd midterm and exam have written portions (the exam written portion was worth 50%). Super interesting course!

I absolutely loved dr. Baird! she's very knowledgable and makes the slides and content entertaining. the midterms were fair and the exam is based solely on the textbook so its an easy A if you study! I would definitely take her class again

LOVED her class! The textbook is a waste of money. If you attend class and take detailed notes you will get an easy A. Her lectures are super interesting and she's also hilarious! She is clearly passionate about what she teaches. Highly recommend her as a prof

She's a great teacher! Her slides don't have everything on them so you'll have to pay attention but that doesn't matter because she makes the lectures entertaining, she shows lots of cute videos of babies and her tests are fair. Study and you'll definitely pass.

Baird is great at conveying information in a very interesting way that makes the material come to life. She is funny, engaging, and uses all kinds of learning tools to best enhance learning. For PSY1101 you'll need the text and to read it because a large portion of your grade comes form the book. Great prof.

One of uOttawa's best professors. Attend class and take notes of everything she says, she gives great help in terms of assignments and exams and even reiterates key information to help you succeed. Read the textbook and ask questions if you're stuck on anything. Definitely take Baird for statistics if you can!

Dr. Baird is the sweetest! She made stats 1 easy to understand. She simplifies the contents and repeats things so that you can get it. Definitely o to DGDs, they help a lot.  She's so nice and stylish! I just wish she taught stats 2 too. Definitely take stats with her!!!

Good teacher. Knows her material. Will post the power points online but her explanations are way better than the textbook. But with that being said, the textbook will be your best friend for the exams. So, be ready to read and study more than just your notes and slides.

Really nice prof. Humorous in a subtle way which makes lectures enjoyable. Most of the info you need is on the slides she posts online, but she does add helpful comments/explanations in class. Knows the material extremely well. Very approachable. Only graded on two midterms and the final exam, so no other opportunities to boost your grade.

Prof Baird is amazing. She absolutely loves and knows what she's talking about for psychopathology. She covers absolutely everything but does emphasize and put weight on her areas of expertise. Lectures are amazing, you must go if you want to pass and know what she expects/is planning plus they're just really interesting. Take this prof if you can!

You need to go to class to pass the class! She's a great prof,  and her lectures were so interesting. She's very intelligent and there's a lot to be learned. She does 2 midterms, a paper and final. Half MC; Half short/long answer. She isn't great with one on one help, don't waste time asking. Best prof to take for psychopathology BY FAR, very fair!

She is amazing. I exited out of my online midterm accidentally before having the chance to complete it. I emailed her explaining what had happened, and she ended up prorating my exam. Very understanding prof and responds to emails quickly! Would definitely recommend.
Easy midterms, all multiple choice. Midterms are based on lectures, not the textbook, recommend attending. Final is on the textbook, so be sure to keep up with readings.
Brenda is amazing ! Cristal clear concerning what she wants and very funny !

She's OK! She had two midterms & final. Midterm 1 was only MCQs. Midterm 2 & final had MCQs & short/long answers. Expects lots of detail for written responses (long answers worth a lot, ranging from 10-20 marks). Memorize everything on slides & read the parts she talks about in great detail in the textbook. She can be a little rude but fair prof.

My all time favourite prof. She is hilarious and her lectures are always clear. It is important to attend class because she does touch on things that aren't in the textbook and usually explains concepts better than the book anyway.  I would go out of my way to take another class of hers.

Then entire course was multiple choice but some of the questions are on content that she never talked about. Her lectures are pretty good and she uses blackboard really well. I'd take her class again.

Best prof for stats! She saved my grade with how helpful and clear she was about the whole course. She wouldn't move on to another topic until everyone understood the material. Gives assignments right before midterms, and practice midterms to help you get the best grade possible. Truly encourage anyone to take her if you are taking stats! Amazing.

Amazing professor!!!! She saved my life in stats. I am horrible in math and was so nervous to take this class but ended up getting an A all because of her. Her teaching style is awesome and she makes sure you understand what she is teaching.  I highly recommend taking stats with her if you are not strong in math.

Professor Baird makes the classes so much more interesting! Easy pass if you attend class. Final exam for PSY1101 is tough since everything is based off of the book and she does not cover everything, but her midterms are super easy! Pay attention to examples she uses as they are most likely on the midterm!

Dr. Baird taught this class well. I was interested during the majority of her lectures. The midterm and exam were a mix of in class lectures and the textbook so study both equally. A fairly standard Psych class but I was happy with it.

She's a really great prof, with a good sense of humour and loves teaching psych. She also tells the best stories that relate to that day's lecture, although sometimes she will call you out if you ask a "stupid" question. Regardless, she's one of my favourite profs and she's extremely helpful.

I found her to be rude and unapproachable. Her assignments were ridiculous and pointless. Her tests were very long especially the second midterm. Do not recommend. As a prof she is ok, fairly clear, material isn't too difficult. Her lectures were very boring and she posts the slides.

Her tests are super reasonable, read the textbook, show up to most classes, and you'll do great. There is no extra credit, so be careful. She's a bit rude sometimes, a touch unapproachable. That being said, she's not quite as good as she says she is, she likes to toot her own horn about how great she is at teaching, but she's an okay teacher.

Attend all classes and take good notes. Study that and you will surely do well (textbook is not needed). On top of that, the lectures are very interesting and crystal clear explanations are provided. Will also allow you to defer an exam if you have a good reason for it. Excellent overall.

You have to read one chapter of a big book by week, Brenda is always there for you, very comprehensive, she is crystal clear in her explanations and gives you the "Why?" of a statistical formula, so you can understand the logic under it. She's funny and she makes statistics INTERESTING, yes you read correctly! TAKE HER

Clearly loves what she's teaching. Very engaged and loves to chat with the students after class, show videos and crack jokes. Knows her material well and the tests are easy (the first one is all multiple choice, the second has some short answers and the exam is easy if you studied). One of the best teachers I've had so far.

Excellent prof, her lectures are interesting, doesn't read off the slides and knows what she's talking about. Really funny, she covers mostly what's in the book too so as long as you show up and take good notes you're golden. Tests (2 midterms and 1 final) are really straight forward. Fair grader.

Professor is clear in her expectations and is a very engaging lecturer. She is hilarious and obviously very knowledgeable on the subject. There were two tests and a final. I did not do my readings or attend classes and managed an 80% on both tests. Manageable class. Great elective or great choice for a prof if the class is required for you!

Baird is an awesome prof! She is very clear on what she expects of you. She teaches the material well, and her exams are fair. She is also super funny, and tells the best stories! Overall, one of my favourite profs

If you ask a dumb question she wont baby you- she will be quick to call you out and put you down. Most people have learned to just keep their questions to themselves but those who haven't make the class entertaining. Besides that, she's a really great prof, with a good sense of humour and seems to really love teaching psych.

Good prof, ok course. Marked on two midterms (mostly multiple choice), a paper, and the final exam. You should read the textbook before the exams. Kind of difficult, but if you study hard you'll get a good mark.
I love how she teaches the material. You definitely have to listen and take notes in class-you can't just go by slides.
Horrible person. She made my life hell and enjoyed it..

This course is manageable, and an A is very possible with enough hard work and efficient reading. The prof is a great lecturer; she explains the material very clearly and tries relating it to real-life situations, which is an excellent teaching method. I highly recommend her for any psychology course.

She's an OK teacher. She knows her stuff and explains well in class. However the exams are not easy and sometimes don't reflect on what we've seen in class. Really have to read the textbook by ourselves. She can sometimes be rude when students answer questions.

I took a course she was teaching at Carleton. Excellent lecturer; explains things thoroughly. Made me feel pretty unintelligent with anything I approached her with outside of class. During lectures she's very helpful and a lot less rude. She won't embarrass you in front of 500 people. Do your readings.

Good Professor ; knew her stuff. Does not go out of her way to help students; just does her job and nothing more.Not very approachable when it comes to extra questions; do not ask her about your program or any advice on career planning. Other professors seem to be more helpful when  it comes to those little extra questions.
She's great at lecturing and teaching. I found her pretty condescending though, one-on-one. I stopped asking her questions because she made me feel like an idiot. :/

Took stats the semester before with another prof and dropped out halfway through cause i was failing with 30's. In Brenda's class i averaged an 80. She is amazing! Dont need the book much, use the study guide! Doing assignments helps so much for the midterms.  Just choose this prof, shes perfect!

Amazing prof. She clearly explains everything. Make sure you attend class and you WILL understand everything. No need to buy the expensive text book, simply purchase the study guide which gives clear step by step instructions. Study Guide + Class Attendance = at least a B grade.

I took the "deadly" stats with her and I am so grateful! if you fail this class or get  bad grade, it's actually because you didn't do the readings. doing the actual math part.. is probably 30% of her 60 mp midterms and 70 mp on exam. She explains everything SO clearly and VERY possible to get a A+ in this class. DO THE READINGS!!! lab was useless
She is good when it comes to teaching and explaining concept you need to know.  Exams are fair.  However, she is very rude when it comes to answering students questions.

One of my favourite professors at this university! She is interesting and funny - the lectures are always engaging and I learned a lot. Be sure to go to all the classes since the PPTs are not all filled out. The exam has some tricky multiple choice questions but it is very fair overall. Great class!

She was a very knowledgeable and lively professor. Her tests were straightforward but for the long answer she was very specific so my advice would be to read the textbook and know the terms. The lectures are good for concepts because she helps with her many anecdotal examples.

Very interested in the material she's teaching and explains it very well. Her lectures don't match up to the textbook very much since she brings in her own content. Attendance is ESSENTIAL for midterms but you won't need to study anything besides notes! Final is pure textbook - DON'T RELY ON NOTES ONLY, YOU WON'T DO WELL! Easy A+ :)

Awesome Prof. I took 1101/1102 two years ago and will be taking her Psychopathology class this coming year! Her teaching is good because she makes things interesting. She informs you about what to expect on the exams. And is very entertaining! Love her class! I'd try to take as many of her classes as I can!

Dr. baird required us to know a lot of material but the way she teaches and how she explains what is on her exams is INCREDIBLE, i wish she taught every course at uottawa! I give her my highest recommendation
Dr.Baird is excellent prof. Take any course with her.
I HEARD POSITIVE FEED BACKS FROM MY FRIENDS WHO TAKE PSYCHOLOGY WITH PROFESSOR BAIRD AND REALLY SHE IS A MAZING PROF. STUDY HARD FOR HER CLASS AND HAVE FUN.

Dr. Baird doesn't need any evaluation at the end of her course. For me as a student from Saint Paul University I benefited a lot from her classes. With her experiences in the Rehab Center for 15 years she provided me with a valuable lesson. I invite you to take any class with her.
Dr. Baird is an excellent professor to teach Psychology. She makes me love psychology as a majof study.

Prof. Baird is unique in her method of teaching which makes the class very interesting and you can not feel the time. She makes us thing critically about her daily class questions and she is very clever in choosing those questions. I never forget what she taught me and how she helped me to study better for psychology.

Great and interesting professor. Writes her own midterms, which are much more difficult than the school written final, though she doesn't cover everything in the textbook, so make sure to read it before the final.
one of the best profs i ever had, luv her

she is hilarious, and after the 2nd midterm going to class is useless, bc the final is based on txtbk only, but the room was full. Her examples are funny.vshe wears the cutest clothes. i suggest buying a used txtbk. she does powerpoint slides (she post them on webCT) which are guides, not notes. go to class, but make notes from txtbk. class avg~75%
She's funny.

AMAZING PROF!! I love how she posted slides and showed videos. Very important to use the textbooks and her slides for all mid-terms and exams even though every prof says the mid-terms are based on in-class lectures, i learned that reading the chapters help "fill in the blanks" to understanding. If you can be flexable with your sched. choose her!!!!
Love her. Amazing sense of humour, really helpful, seems to actually care whether her students do well. Tells good (and useful) stories and her outfits are always creative.
Good at explaining things. Has interesting examples.

Dr. Baird is a fantastic prof and defiantly one of my favorites. Her excellent sense of humor and laid back nature makes attending class a true pleasure. Just a word of caution, if you need to leave class early, just let her know ahead of time. Otherwise you may get called out! :P
Decent teacher, but I resent the fact that she chases you out of class if you leave early.
Dr Baird is a great teacher. She is a brilliant lady and has a great knowledge transfer strategy. I would recommend her teaching to anyone.

It's so true about the genetics lectures. They are too simplified and made me cringe a bit at their inaccuracies. It was when we left the science topics and focused on mental disorders that i started becoming interested. Overall she's a pretty stimulating professor who has to put up with a lot of slackers.
her midterms are fair, but do not really prepart you for the final exam wich is a lot harder
Awesome professor. Great lecturer, very intelligent and funny lady. I was never bored in her class.

Great Proff - very funny and friendly, definitely kept our class entertained. She often brings in videos to help explain things that were discussed and was very good about answering questions. Very approachable and very clear in her method of teaching. Her slides do need to be added to, but as long as you attend class it shouldn't be a problem.

AMAZING prof. Pretty much made psych. my favourite class. I looked forward to going to her classes. Very good slides, clear expectations, and she was funny and helpful. All you need to get a good grade is a bit of interest and a decent attendance (you don't want to miss her thorough in-class explanations). Hope to have her again sometime!
She is an ass, so is her TA. Jessica kokins this Ta is the most useless person i have seen!

She's a very good professor and her class is entertaining. A lot like the other psych 1101, the first mid-term is heavy on stuff that was covered in class that is NOT in the textbook. Very important to go to class.
No Comments

Great teacher, very energetic, helpful and funny.  Her slides are very useful.  Go to class, do your readings and you'll pass with flying colors.  She's also very approachable and friendly.  Love this teacher !!
Always kept class interesting. Very clear and to the point.
She is sooo funny and a very fair teacher. Really takes the time to ensure students understand material.
Very informedand made class so interesting

She's the very definition of n ideal prof.She's organized,notes r clear n precise, explains the material exceptionally well, tests r fair,always avail. n willing 2 help u out.2 top it off, she has n incredible personality!Hilarious, charismatic, passionate about psy.She Has the ability 2 make u want 2 b a better student.Honest,real n down to earth!
shes awesome, makes everything clear and simple. funny, and ruined a girl walking out of class one day..which ruled... great prof, made the class fun and interesting.
Nice lady, interesting personality.  Notes are well prepared and her midterms and finals are straight out of her notes.  Read your chapters, and learn her slides, you'll do great!

Ok prof. Notes & exams are prepared, exams were ok too. I've noticed that for some of the negative comments they tend to be challenged (by her?) and are replied back to (by her?). If yes, maybe should not take comments personally but as a means to improve. As a budding psychologist, shouldnt place her self-esteem on a couple of negative comments

Professor Baird was really fun to have, certainly passionate about her subject.  Textbook was no use until final, then it was everything.  Read the chapters as she goes through for results and least stress.  Slides were available online, but don't skip or neglect notes - the slides often had only the main points with no explainations attached.

I really enjoyed the way her class was taught. Lectures were clearly presented and I was sufficiently prepared to find no surprises on exams. She is a very helpful prof, only one complaint, regarding a mark of 58 on my term paper, which is unusually low for me, especially considering how much work I put into this paper, and time spent revising it a

At the beginning, had a great impression, seemed funny, straight-forward, easy-going teacher, as the semester progressed she went back on her instructions and was not very nice. One day had to leave her class early, was as quiet as possible, but she still insisted on stopping the lecture to say bye in a rude tone to me... pfft don't take her class!
Exams were fair, 3hrs class usually ended lasted only 2hrs.  Study her notes more than the text book.
excellent prof
Funny, we thought it was excellent, and who are the undergrad scientsists anyway????

Very very easy midterms, but any scientists in the class will just die from her explanations of genetics. Don't listen to anything she says about DNA. Nice prof overall though, when she sticks to psych stuff.
No Comments
She's a pretty standard example of a great prof. Clear explanations, interesting, knowledgable, and cheerful. Great class, great prof.
Brenda Baird is an awesome prof!!!She knows her stuff incredibly well and she will help you if you need help right.Anyone who wants to take psy, I strongly rec. to take it with Baird.Great Prof!!!
Clear explanations. She relates the material to her own life a lot of the time, which is very helpful. She is a good prof to get.

She is an awesome teacher. Very friendly and funny. Makes lectures very enjoyable, especially at 8 30 in the morning. She wants everyone to do well, she tells you exactly what is on the midterms-most ppl got A's. *Two thumbs up!!* Get her if you can!!

This prof knows her stuff. SHE WANTS YOU TO SUCCEED and she does everything in her power to help you do so.A tip would be to attend class and take notes. She explains concepts clearly and you actually RETAIN some of the info you are presented (unlike other Profs' useless lectures).Lectures are enjoyable and fun to attend at 8:30 in the morning.
awesome, very clear
